The paper deals with the problem of private computation, which involves distributed servers and privacy-preserving computation. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to information theory (cs.IT), cryptography (cs.CR), distributed systems (cs.DS), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and complexity theory (cs.CC). The focus on capacity and communication rates also suggests a connection to information theory and communication theory. Therefore, cs.IT and cs.CR are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.DS, cs.DC, and cs.CC.
